## PART 10: KILL CONDITIONS & RISK MANAGEMENT\
\
### Kill Conditions (Stop and Pivot If...)\
\
1. **Beta sprint completion rate is below 40%.** If fewer than 40% of beta users complete the first sprint, the product mechanism doesn't work and needs fundamental redesign.\
\
2. **90-day retention is below 35%.** If you can't keep more than 1 in 3 users past 90 days, the unit economics will never work at any price point.\
\
3. **50 sales conversations yield zero conversions.** If people love the concept but won't pay, the willingness-to-pay assumption is wrong.\
\
4. **Monthly churn exceeds 10% for 3+ consecutive months after Month 6.** Early churn is expected as you optimize. If it doesn't improve, the retention mechanics are fundamentally broken.\
\
5. **CAC exceeds $150 and LTV is below $500.** The 3:1 LTV:CAC ratio is non-negotiable for sustainable growth.\
\
### Risk Mitigation Summary\
\
| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\
|------|------------|--------|------------|\
| Churn kills unit economics | Likely | Fatal | Sprint structure, pause protocol, squad bonds, AI re-engagement |\
| ChatGPT absorbs use case | Possible | Severe | Peer squad mechanism is structurally unreplicable by 1-on-1 AI |\
| Can't acquire users profitably | Likely | Severe | Start with organic channels (content, podcasts), validate before scaling paid |\
| Audience too vague | Possible | Severe | Launch in single niche (founders), expand only after validation |\
| AI facilitation feels hollow | Possible | Manageable | Test extensively in beta, iterate on prompts, let humans carry the accountability weight |\
| Platform dependency (Discord) | Possible | Manageable | Build custom app once validated, don't over-invest in platform-specific features |\
